Package: metaTransportEngine
Type: Package
Title: Aggregate-Data Meta-Analysis with Transport to Target Populations
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("OpenAI", "Codex", email = "noreply@openai.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Fits frequentist and Bayesian hierarchical meta-regression models
    that transport aggregate study evidence to one or more target
    populations using observed study-level modifiers. Provides overlap
    diagnostics, extrapolation scores, leave-one-out instability checks,
    bias sensitivity summaries, and export helpers.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.2.0)
Imports:
    ggplot2,
    jsonlite,
    metafor,
    rstan
Suggests:
    knitr,
    pkgdown,
    pkgload,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
SystemRequirements: C++17, make (required for Stan model compilation)
VignetteBuilder: knitr
